The paper discusses the application of machine learning techniques to address key problems in IoT wireless communications, with an emphasis on its ad hoc networking aspect. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. Additionally, the paper extensively discusses machine learning techniques, indicating that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also discusses the use of wireless communication protocols, indicating that it could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) category. Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of these techniques in hardware, suggesting that it could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category.
